        </partsinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="4">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage, personal injury, or death:</para>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>park the vehicle on a flat level surface</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>set the parking brake</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>turn the engine off and chock the wheels</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>allow the engine to cool before performing the Service Procedure.</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the heater pipe mounting bracket (Figure 1), remove the mounting bolt and
                    relocate the mounting bracket and mounting bolt to the lower hole as shown in Figure 1, Item 2.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f049051" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g049051.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Relocate Bracket to Hole 2</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Valve Cover Hole</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Correct Hole in Engine Block</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the bellows of the EGR connector pipe for evidence of contact with the heater
                    pipe bracket (Figure 2).
                </para>
                <seqlist>
                    <item>
                        <para>If there is no evidence of contact, the EGR connector tube does not need to be replaced.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>If there is evidence of contact between the heater pipe bracket and the EGR connector pipe
                            bellows, the EGR connect pipe needs to be replaced. Continue to the next Step.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </seqlist>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f049052" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g049052.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. EGR Connector Pipe Bellows Shown at Arrow</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the EGR connector pipe fasteners, clamps, sensor, seal, and EGR pipe as shown in
                    Figure 3. Retain the fasteners, clamps, sensor, and seal for reuse.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f049053" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g049053.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. EGR Connector Pipe Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. EGR Sensor</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Seal</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install new EGR Connector pipe. Refer to Figure 4 and Table 2.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f049054" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g049054.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Tighten Fasteners and Clamps</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Upper EGR Connector Pipe Cap Screw</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Lower EGR Connector Pipe Cap Screw</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. V-Band</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Clamp</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
